# AutoForge Overview

AutoForge is an AI-native software engineering platform that orchestrates multiple specialized agents through a serial pipeline to design, implement, and verify software projects. It combines a chat-first interface, a structured specification system, and a relay pipeline that routes tasks between profession-specific agents.

## System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph UI["User Interface"]
        Chat[Chat]
        SpecsView[Specs]
        WikiView[Wiki]
        RelayPanel[Relay Pipeline]
    end

    subgraph Orchestrator["Agent Orchestrator"]
        Assistant[Assistant<br/>Intake]
        Architect[Architect<br/>Design]
        Planner[Planner<br/>Plan]
        Coder[Coder<br/>Code]
        Tester[Tester<br/>Verify]
    end

    subgraph Core["Core Services"]
        Provider[Provider<br/>LLM SSE]
        Tools[Tools<br/>FS / Shell]
        ProjectMgr[Project<br/>Workspace]
        Checkpoint[Checkpoint<br/>Durability]
    end

    UI --> Orchestrator
    Orchestrator --> Core
```

